The paper discusses distributed optimization algorithms in machine learning applications, which falls under the category of "Machine Learning" (cs.LG). The paper also proposes building models to capture system level characteristics and convergence rates, which could fall under "Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing" (cs.DC) and "Data Structures and Algorithms" (cs.DS). The paper also discusses challenges in developing such a system, which could fall under "Systems and Control" (cs.SY) and "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE).
